      <h1 class='title'>Animal Health and Welfare Strategy</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 15 July 2003 vol 409 c11WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_11ws' title='Col. 11WS &mdash; HC Deb 15 July 2003 vol 409 c11WS' name='column_11ws' href='#column_11ws' rel='bookmark'>11WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0409P0-02288'>
        <a name='S6CV0409P0_20030715_CWS_2'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-ben-bradshaw' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0409P0_20030715_CWS_2' title='Link to this speech by Mr Ben Bradshaw' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-ben-bradshaw" title="Mr Ben Bradshaw">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (Mr. Ben Bradshaw)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0409P0-02288">I have arranged for copies of the Government's Animal Health and Welfare Strategy for Great Britain to be made available in the Libraries of both Houses. Produced jointly by DEFRA, the Scottish Executive and the Welsh Assembly, the outline strategy is being circulated for public consultation, with a deadline for comments of 31 October.</p><p id="S6CV0409P0-02289">Copies are also available on the DEFRA website at <span class="underline">http://www.defra.gov.uk/animalh</span></p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
